The paper deals with object localization in images, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for localization using combinational class activation maps, which involves designing a network architecture and integrating non-local modules. This suggests that the paper may also belong to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on representative object localization benchmarks, which could place it in categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
